# @param {Integer[]} heights
# @param {Integer[][]} queries
# @return {Integer[]}
def leftmost_building_queries(heights, queries)
    answer = []
    queries.each do |query|
        alice, bob = query
        next_building = [alice, bob].max
        leftmost_meet = -1
        if alice < bob
            (alice..bob).each do |i|
                if heights[i] > heights[alice] && heights[i] > heights[bob]
                    leftmost_meet = i
                    break
                end
            end
        elsif alice > bob
            (bob..alice).each do |i|
                if heights[i] > heights[bob] && heights[i] > heights[alice]
                    leftmost_meet = i
                    break
                end
            end
        else
            leftmost_meet = alice # they are in the same building
        end
        answer.push(leftmost_meet)
    end
    answer
end
